@chapter Invoking @command{usbprog}
@cindex invoking
@cindex version
@cindex options
@cindex usage
@cindex help
@cindex getting help

The format for running the @command{usbprog} program is:

@example
usbprog @var{option} @dots{}
@end example

@code{usbprog} supports the following options:

@c Formatting copied from the Texinfo 4.0 manual.
@table @code
@item --verbose
@itemx -v
Print more information.

@item --help
@itemx -?
Print an informative help message describing the options and then exit
successfully.

@item --usage
Briefly list the options.

@item --version
@itemx -V
Print the version number of @command{usbprog} on the standard output
and then exit successfully.
@end table

